<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COYOTES' TVERDOVSKY A HEALTHY SCRATCH 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS AND BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Coyotes defenseman  &UR; Oleg Tverdovsky, who played in all
82 regular-season games and the first six games of the first-round
Stanley Cup playoff series against St. Louis, was a surprising
healthy scratch from Tuesday night's Game 7 with the Blues.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first playoff game Tverdovsky, who had played in 19
straight postseason games, has missed in his five-year career. When
the scratch was announced, the crowd cheered loudly.
</P>
<P>
   ``We felt our best chance to win the game is with the six
defensemen who will play in front of him,'' General Manager  &UR; Bobby
 &UR; Smith said of Tverdovsky who has had two assists and six penalty
minutes in the series.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes elected to play defensemen  &UR; Teppo Numminen, Jyrki
 &UR; Lumme, Keith Carney, Gerald Diduck, J.J. Daigneault and  &UR; Stan
Neckar. Apparently, the Coyotes thought Neckar would give them a
stronger physical presence.
</P>
<P>
   Tverdovsky will be a restricted Group II free agent at season's
end. He was a restricted free agent two years ago and took part in
a protracted contract holdout that limited his season 46 games.
</P>
<P>
   Smith was asked if he thought the decision to sit Tverdovsky
will affect his desire to return to Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't think so,'' Smith said. ``That's something we will
deal with him during the summer.''
</P>
<P>
   Tverdovsky was unavailable for comment. &QL; 
Ylonen signs &QL; 
The Coyotes have re-signed forward  &UR; Juha Ylonen, who would have
been a restricted free-agent at season's end, to a three-year
contract. Terms were not available.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's OK and I'm very happy,'' Ylonen said.
</P>
<P>
   ``They (Coyotes) came to me about it a month ago and we got in
done about two weeks ago, just before I broke my foot. I'm going to
be in the Valley for a couple weeks after the season, then I'm
going home to Finland for the summer and start working for next
year.'' &QL; 
Adams plays &QL; 
While center  &UR; Jeremy Roenick staged a surprise comeback, so did
second-line left wing  &UR; Greg Adams, whose services have been limited
to two games because of a strained groin.
</P>
<P>
   Adams'return was a game-time decision, but he addressed the
dilemma he was facing Tuesday after the morning skate.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not 100 percent or anywhere near,'' Adams said. ``I want
to go, but at the same time I don't want to take a spot if someone
who's 100 percent can give the team more. That's the decision;
whether I can contribute at 80-85 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ``Once you get in you get caught up in the game.'' &QL; 
Travel dilemma &QL; 
St. Louis management was perplexed entering Game 7. Initially, it
planned to check out of the Ritz-Carlton before the game and either
return home in the event of a loss, or to re-check into the hotel
for the night before leaving for Dallas today to meet the Stars in
the second-round on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   After thinking about it, management thought the Blues might take
it as a poor vote of confidence and decided the team would either
fly to St. Louis or to Dallas after the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``The right message to send your team, if it's a Game 7 and
you're on the road, is to give them six- or seven-days meal
money,'' Coyotes Coach  &UR; Jim Schoenfeld said, laughing. ``If you
give them one day's meal money and wait and see, you're not showing
a lot of faith in your troops.'' &QL; 
Understanding guy &QL; 
Rookie  &UR; Daniel Briere spent three-fourths of the season with the
Coyotes, only to be sent to the AHL Springfield Falcons as the
playoffs approached. He was recalled last week, but has seen no
action and was a spectator Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wish I could be in the lineup, but . . . at the end I wasn't
playing much or playing well,'' he said. ``They went with other
guys. I understand. For me it's a good learning experience to be
here and learn around a Game 7 and gain experience for the
future.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
