   AFFIRMATIVE-ACTION (San Francisco) _ The city has won the first
Proposition 209-based court challenge to its affirmative action
contracting ordinance, which requires city contractors to set goals
for minority and female subcontractors. But the court did not rule
on whether the city's minority business ordinance violated Prop.
209, the voter-approved ban on race and sex preferences. By GREGORY
LEWIS.
