told _ to mark Earth Week, the tribute to the environment
celebrated in late April. The game is backed by the National Park
Foundation, which gets a percentage of the proceeds from sales. But
there's something a little off-kilter here. The game lets people
buy up national parks. By EDVINS BEITIKS.
