<P>
   NATO-CLARK (Brussels) _ NATO supreme commander Gen. Wesley K.
Clark is in a job very few in the US Army would have predicted he
would get, and many didn't want him to get. Clark doesn't win
popularity contests in the Army. By Kevin Cullen 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   KLA-VOLUNTEERS (Durres, Albania) _ Much as non-Spaniards flocked
to Spain to fight against fascism before World War II,
non-Albanians by the hundreds are flocking to sign up with the KLA.
By Susan Milligan. 950 words.
</P>
