<SLUG> BC-FOUNTAINS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOUNTAINS ARE BACK, ON A SMALLER SCALE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By FRANCES INGRAHAM  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ There's nothing quite as soothing as the sound of
water trickling from a fountain. The sound has soothed people since
ancient Greece, where public fountains were the norm.
</P>
<P>
   The earliest evidence of an artificial fountain dates to 4,000
B.C. in what is now Iran.
</P>
<P>
   Early fountains built above natural springs were thought to have
magical powers, and many were enhanced with statues of gods and
goddesses.
</P>
<P>
   From the 1500s to the 1700s, elaborate pumping systems were
created for cascading water and powerful jets of water. During this
time, many of the famous Renaissance fountains were built, such as
the Trevi Fountain in Rome and those at the Palace of Versailles
near Paris.
</P>
<P>
   Since the 1960s, modern technology has utilized computerized
pumps to control the flow of water as well as the lighting.
</P>
<P>
   Fountains were originally used in public spaces. By the 1800s
and early 1900s they began gracing the grounds of private estates
in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Today, the residential fountain is used primarily as decoration,
and instead of being the focal point as in earlier formal estate
gardens, it's often incorporated as one part of the overall
landscape or garden design.
</P>
<P>
   Contemporary catalogs and garden centers offer a vast selection
of free-standing fountains that are formal, informal or whimsical
in nature. They also come with their own pumps.
</P>
<P>
   For the energy-minded, there are even solar-powered pond
fountains, which start at around $129 for a 12-volt pump,
fountainhead and four attachments that vary the spray pattern, from
Smith &AMP; Hawken, 800-776-3336. Small pumps start at $10 and go up
according to the amount of water that is to be pumped per minute.
There are also fountain kits, which start at about $60.
</P>
<P>
   Contemporary fountains come in a range of materials from cast
resins that simulate bronze to stone, concrete and marble, which
can cost in the thousands.
</P>
<P>
   Depending on the size and detailing, finished and unfinished
resin fountains cost anywhere from a few hundred dollars to $1,500,
according to Olsen's Nursery and Greenhouses in Slingerlands, N.Y.
Fountains are so tranquil that they have even made their way to
patios, balconies and indoors to the tabletop. Many of the small
fountains are vase-like or works of sculpted art and are powered by
a recirculating pump and an electrical outlet.
</P>
<P>
   Interior fountains also vary in price depending on their
complexity, with many starting at approximately $50.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-05-99 1326EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990505.0114 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-05 13:32 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5094 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TURN-OFF-TV-HNS &LR;      05-05 0349
