<P>
   This column moved today:
</P>
<P>
   BERNARD GLADSTONE'S ``HOME IMPROVEMENT QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS''
for Sun., May 23, 1999, which included:
</P>
<P>
   -How to repair and replace mortar in brick joints using special
tuck pointing tools (comes with illustration).
</P>
<P>
   -How to treat vinyl-clad aluminum siding.
</P>
<P>
   -How to fix a fireplace that fills the room with smoke.
</P>
<P>
   _How to dig a trench above house to capture downhill flow of
invasive moisture.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: Art work accompanies all Gladstone ``Home Improvement''
columns.
</P>
