<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini views
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Babe: Pig in the City'' (G) _ This little piggy has a
sequel. But while most of the main players are reunited, some of
the magic has worn off. The movie welcomes us back to the world of
talking Babe and his farm friends, plus the farming couple the
Hoggetts (James Cromwell and Magda Szubanski). But the sequel sends
Babe and the Missus to the big city for a series of misadventures
that fill the screen with all sorts of talking animals. Problem is,
Babe himself gets lost in the crowd. Even so, it's visually one of
the liveliest, loveliest movies of 1998, giving us the sort of
fantasy metropolis any bright-eyed kid would love. Grade: B -
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Lilies'' (R) _ Directed by John Greyson, who gave us the
spectacularly, um, unique AIDS musical ``Zero Patience'' a few
years back, ``Lilies'' is a lush celebration of young love and
melodrama. Drunk on its own romanticism, it combines Tennessee
Williams, Jean Genet, ``Marat/Sade'' and the more homoerotic
elements of the Catholic church. It's a triumph more of style than
substance, as an aging bishop in 1952 is compelled to watch a cast
of prisoners perform a stage version, telling of the cleric's own
young betrayal of two teen male friends who fell in love. All the
roles are played by men, resulting in a Brent Carver's beautiful
performance as one boy's deluded mother. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   Notable videos on sale
</P>
<P>
   Westerns: ``A Fistful of Dollars,'' ``The Badlanders,'' ``Dodge
City,'' ``The Fastest Gun Alive'' and ``The Kentuckian,'' $14.95.
</P>
<P>
   Kids: ``Puss in Boots,'' an original animated feature, $16.95.
</P>
<P>
   DVD: ``Babe: Pig in the City,'' $29.98. ``The 'Burbs,'' ``The
Land Before Time,'' $24.98. The DTS versions of ``Blues Brothers
2000,'' ``The Boxer,'' ``Out of Sight'' and ``Primary Colors,''
$34.98. ``Monty Python's Life of Brian'' and ``Time Bandits,''
collector's editions, $24.98.
</P>
<P>
   Ol' blue eyes: ``Frank Sinatra: The Best Is Yet to Come,'' an
authorized retrospective of the entertainer's life, $19.95.
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
