<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on James Cromwell
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   (``Babe: Pig in the City'')
</P>
<P>
   ``Babe'' (1995) Dancing a jig to make his little piggy feel
better. It also didn't hurt that Cromwell got an Oscar nomination.
</P>
<P>
   ``L.A. Confidential'' (1997) Overseeing Guy Pearce and Russell
Crowe as chief of police in this twisty film noir.
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Trek: First Contact'' (1996) Boozing it up as a
20th-century inventor.
</P>
<P>
   Babe: Pig in the City
</P>
<P>
   Babe and Farmer Hoggett (James Cromwell) reture to a very proud
Esme Hoggett (Magda Szubanski)
</P>
<P>
   (copyright)1998 Universal City Studios
</P>
