<HEADLINE>
AVERT YOUR EYES, FANBOY 
</HEADLINE>
  (With CIR-STAR-WARS) 
(js) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   As the May 19 release of ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom
Menace'' approaches, the Internet is buzzing with rumors and
conjecture about how the story will unfold. Here are examples of
some rumors, called ``spoilers,'' recently found on The Force.net
(www.theforce.net). If you would rather not know what happens in
the film until you see it in a theater, you should read no further.
</P>
<P>
   _ Obi-Wan Kenobi (Ewan McGregor) and Qui-Gon Jinn (Liam Neeson),
Jedi knights, board a Federation battleship and realize an invasion
army has been sent by Darth Sidious to Naboo, a swamp planet.
</P>
<P>
   _ On Naboo, they team up with Jar Jar Binks, a man-size,
speaking, frog-like creature.
</P>
<P>
   _ Obi-Wan Kenobi and Qui-Gon Jinn rescue Queen Amidala (Natalie
Portman), the young ruler of Naboo, who is being pressured by the
Federation to sign a treaty that would legitimize its occupation of
her planet.
</P>
<P>
   _ Darth Vader appears as a child named Anakin Skywalker (Jake
Lloyd). Early evidence of The Force: Anakin is good at pod racing,
a popular sport in which drivers are pulled by giant tethered jet
engines.
</P>
<P>
   _ In the climactic battle, Qui-Gon is killed by Darth Maul (Ray
Park), an evil warrior who fights with a double-ended light saber.
Darth Maul is then killed by Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
</TEXT>
