<HEADLINE>
KEY RATES 
</HEADLINE>
  (xx) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the daily key rates from The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   -----------------Wednesday ----Tuesday ----Year Ago
</P>
<P>
   PRIME RATE ---------- 7.75 ------ 7.75 ------- 8.50
</P>
<P>
   DISCOUNT RATE ------- 4.50 ------ 4.50 ------- 5.00
</P>
<P>
   FEDERAL FUNDS(x) ---- 4.69 ------ 4.71 ------- 4.23
</P>
<P>
   3-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 4.47 ------ 4.48 ------- 4.34
</P>
<P>
   6-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 4.47 ------ 4.50 ------- 4.37
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. INF(xx) 3.84 ------ 3.86 ------- 3.89
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. NOTES - 5.39 ------ 5.40 ------- 4.71
</P>
<P>
   30-YR. TREAS. BONDS - 5.70 ------ 5.71 ------- 5.16
</P>
<P>
   TELEPHONE BONDS ----- 7.46 ------ 7.48 ------- 6.84
</P>
<P>
   MUNICIPAL BONDS(xxx) 5.31 ------ 5.32 ------- 5.17
</P>
<P>
   (x) Estimated daily average, Dow Jones Markets
</P>
<P>
   (xx) Realized dollar amount rises with inflation
</P>
<P>
   (xxx) Municipal Bond Index, The Bond Buyer
</P>
<P>
   Sources: Salomon Smith Barney; Bridge Information Systems; The
Bond Buyer
</P>
