<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-ATLANTARECORDS _ ATLANTA _ The attorney general's office, in
its strongest declaration yet that the Atlanta Olympic records are
public, has asked under threat of lawsuit for Olympic officials to
turn over files that they consider private. (Turner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (s) Sports and (a) General News categories.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-CARDS06 _ ATLANTA _ Braves-Cardinals game story.
(Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 1:10 p.m. EDT
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES-NOTES06 _ ATLANTA _ Braves notebook. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NUHN-MINORLEAGUES _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Jim and Paul are minor
league devotees. They grew up in Toledo, thus their allegiance to
the Mud Hens. Jim says he's ``over 40.'' Paul is 39. That was Jim
walking around Dayton's Courthouse Square in his Mud Hens' uniform
on Monday when the new Dayton minor league team unveiled its name
(Dragons), uniforms and logo, ``just to show my support for minor
league baseball,'' he said. Every year for the past 11 years, the
brothers have made one week-long trip and another extended weekend
trip to minor league games, mostly but not always following farm
clubs of the Tigers. Their count is now 11 leagues and 63 parks.
When Dayton starts next spring, it's going to be a nice, easy 64th.
(Nuhn, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-DREW _ Georgia native J.D. Drew is showing signs of coming
into his own with the Cardinals. (Rosen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MIAMI-WOODEN _ DAVIE, Fla. _ Shawn Wooden not only
participated in the Dolphins' mini-camp last week, the team's
former starting strong safety talked about how his left knee had
recovered from the injury that forced him to miss most of last
season. ``It's almost 100 percent,'' he said. Almost. (Woods, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-SENIOR _ Bruce Fleisher is like many successful Senior Tour
golfers. After being a PGA Tour journeyman, he found his
comfortable niche on the Senior Tour and has turned that niche into
three 1999 victories and a comfortable living. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-GASENIORS _ Georgians Larry Nelson, Allen Doyle and Joe
Inman have served the state well on the Senior Tour _ another
victory or two away from outright dominance. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15-18.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-ITEMS _ An odds/ends golf pacckage. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   GLF-NOTES _ Nationwide notes column. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-DOYLE _ LA GRANGE, GA. _ When Allen Doyle headed to the
Senior PGA Tour at the beginning of the season, he was hoping to
earn some pocket change to help send his kids to college. He has
done that. In three short months, Doyle has earned almost $1
million after two victories _ including a major _ and several top-5
finishes. His success has been so dramatic that the grass at
Doyle's old driving range in LaGrange, Ga., isn't looking so green
anymore. (Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 55. MOVED. WITH
PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-PLAYOFFS-ADVANCE _ Advance on second round of NHL playoffs.
(Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HKN-NHL-CAPSULES _ Capsules on Eastern and Western Conference
semifinals. (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-NOTES _ International soccer notes column. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   MISCELLANEOUS
</P>
<P>
   FEN-HUMMER-FENCING _ The stance is slightly balletic, front foot
pointed straight forward, back foot turned at a right angle. I
assume it without requiring an orthopedic device, a fine start. The
dress is straight from the Hannibal Lecter collection _ a white
coat that is just two straps away from being a straitjacket and a
bird cage that fits snugly over the head. I might borrow the outfit
the next time the dental hygienist tries to get at me. The language
is like something stolen from a good wine list. En garde. Epee.
Maitre d'Armes. The list of French fighting words can't be very
long, but they're all here. The instructor, well, he has just
raised his blunted foil to me and said something along the lines
of, ``You have sullied my sister and for this you must die!'' Gene
Gettler was only kidding. At least he seemed to be. If he wasn't, I
think I might well have sullied my shorts. This is my introduction
to fencing. It's not just for European fops anymore. (Hummer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
