<P>
   EDITORS: The N.Y. Times Photo Service has moved the following
photos on Wednesday, May5, which are strongly recommended:
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) CAGRANE, Macedonia -- May 5, 1999 -- KOSOVO-MASSACRE-2,
5-05 -- A woman weeps while recalling her memories of an alleged
massacre in Slovinje, in Yugoslavia's Kosovo province, after
arriving at a refugee camp earlier this week. When the bloodletting
began in Kosovo, the Serbs of Slovinje told their ethnic Albanian
neighbors they had nothing to fear from the marauding army or
paramilitary. Last Friday, two mass graves were dug up in Slovinje.
(Andrew Testa/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) CAGRANE, Macedonia -- May 5, 1999 -- KOSOVO-MASSACRE-1,
5-05 -- A 34 year old barber from Slovinje, who was a witness to
the reported massacres, lies in a tent at a refugee camp earlier
this week. The man said he was shot while fleeing from Serb
paramilitary forces and was awaiting surgery at the camp. (Andrew
Testa/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
