   SCI-ORGAN-DONATION (Washington) _ Early next year, Pennsylvania
will become the first state in the nation to offer a financial
incentive _ roughly $300 _ for the donation of organs. By Sheryl
Gay Stolberg. 1,200 words. (MOVED)
</P>
<P>
   TV-HOME-IMPROVEMENT (Los Angeles) _ Compare the last episode of
``Seinfeld'' with the recent taping of the final episode of ``Home
Improvement,'' a prime-time hit on ABC for the past eight seasons.
After a tearful Tim Allen, the star, told a joke for a cast and
crew drenched in tears, they taped a slightly maudlin story,
scheduled to air on May 25, in which Allen's character reaffirms
his love for his wife and family, and his loyal sidekick finds the
love that had long eluded him, lending the closing a poignant moral
gravity. The episode is touching, and a historical relic, as the
traditional family sitcom goes the way of the western. By James
Sterngold. 1,587 words.
</P>
</TEXT>
