<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, May 6, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact David Brady at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   ABSENT-STUDENTS (Los Angeles) _ Rumors of racially motivated
violence at schools prompted thousands of suburban Los Angeles
students to stay home and police to assign extra patrols at
campuses for Cinco de Mayo on Wednesday. Several San Fernando
Valley schools reported drastically low attendance figures,
including Chatsworth High School, where more than half of the
students skipped. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   REMEDIAL-CLASSES (Los Angeles) _ About 1,100 students at
California State University, Northridge, are retaking remedial
English and math classes and face expulsion if they cannot pass by
September, under a new rule for all CSU freshmen. Out of CSUN's
freshman class of 2,100 students, only about 400 passed an
admissions exam exempting them from remedial classes. By Robert
Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   CSU-FACULTY (Los Angeles) _ Led by a California State
University, Northridge, economics professor, a group of
non-unionized faculty members are opposing a bill by state Sen.
Jack O'Connell, D-Santa Barbara, that would require all faculty of
the California State University to pay dues to the California
Faculty Association union. They argue an agency shop only boosts
coffers for the union. By Sharline Chiang. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ROCKETTE-SEARCH (Los Angeles) _ A casting call drew hundreds of
young dancers to learn tap, ballet and jazz combinations during
this year's auditions for the Rockettes' U.S. tour. Audition
results will be announced in June.by Michael Coit. (Will move in
the ``a'' national and ``e'' entertainment news files.)
</P>
<P>
   MACYS-SPINOFF (Los Angeles) _ Tapping into one of the hottest
areas in retailing, Macy's is spinning off a new chain of
free-standing stores specializing in beauty products, candles and
other ``impulse'' merchandise _ and using a local shopping center
as its Southern California testing ground. By Enrique Rivero. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CHASENS-PUBLIC (Los Angeles) _ Soon you can own a stake in the
night spot that's been a favorite haunt of stars from Humphrey
Bogart to Madonna. A Marina del Rey, Calif., venture capital firm
plans to take Chasen's public in the coming weeks. By Gregory J.
Wilcox. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FHS-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Foundation Health Systems Inc.
reported a healthy increase in earnings Wednesday on growth at its
HealthNet HMO. Although its shares had a 10 percent run-up Tuesday
in anticipation of the strong earnings, shares of the Woodland
Hills-based company are well-below their all-time high because of a
difficult 1998.By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial
news file.)
</P>
