   BROKERAGE-INDICT (New York) _ The Manhattan district attorney,
Robert M. Morgenthau, has indicted Duke &AMP; Co., a defunct New York
brokerage firm; its chairman, Victor Wang, and 17 former Duke
employees, charging that the firm was a criminal enterprise that
conspired with other brokerages to manipulate the prices of six
small stocks. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
