<HEADLINE>
FIRST THING, UP IN THE SKY ...
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you searched high and low _ through heaven and hell, for
instance _ and you couldn't find a Cliffs Notes for the Good Book,
you'll be elated at news of ``The Complete Idiot's Guide to the
Bible'' (Alpha Books, $16.95), in which  &UR; Jim Bell &LR;  and  &UR; Stan &LR; 
 &UR; Campbell &LR;  make breezy reading of the text.
</P>
<P>
   One typical translation _ ``dumbed down,'' says Jump magazine _
converts ``What sayeth thou?'' to ``Whatcha think about this?''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ACT UP founder  &UR; Larry Kramer &LR; , at work on a new book, told the
New York Post he will reveal that  &UR; Abraham Lincoln  &LR; was gay, a fact
he says has ``been kept a secret by stodgy heterosexual
historians.''
</P>
<P>
   _ At BookExpo America in Los Angeles last weekend,  &UR; Renata Polt &LR; 
of Berkeley was talking to an Israeli publisher about buying rights
to her book, ``A Thousand Kisses: A Grandmother's Holocaust
Letters.'' He told her, ``People in Israel don't buy books on the
Holocaust. We want books on management strategies.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Roseanne  &LR; has a fear of anyone touching her toes, says Marie
Claire magazine, and  &UR; Johnny Depp  &LR; is afraid of clowns.
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Cameron Reagan &LR; , 20-year-old grandson of former President
Ronald Reagan, has been sentenced to six months in jail after
pleading no contest to charges of receiving property stolen in auto
burglaries. His lawyer had argued he needed the money because his
parents had thrown him out of the house, and he is suffering from
adult attention deficit disorder.
</P>
<P>
   _ Supermodel  &UR; Linda Evangelista  &LR; turned down an invitation to
appear on the cover of a Harper's Bazaar issue devoted to the
memory of late editor  &UR; Liz Tilberis &LR;  because ``Linda knew she
wouldn't be able to handle it properly,'' her agent told the New
York Post. ``She is too emotionally distraught.'' The issue will
feature photos donated by  &UR; Patrick Demarchelier &LR; ,  &UR; Richard Avedon &LR; ,
 &UR; Steven Meisel &LR; ,  &UR; Bruce Weber &LR;  and others. All ad proceeds will be
donated to the Ovarian Cancer Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TREND-WATCHING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Thirty-one percent of the readers of Mademoiselle magazine say
they feel more mature than their parents. And according to P.O.V.,
there are three times as many cattle in the United States as there
are human senior citizens. And Iconoculture Inc., whose theory is
reported in the Wall Street Journal, says that because of ``so many
casualties out there,'' a long first marriage is a status symbol.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, a poll on morals taken by Shell Oil found that 30
percent viewed  &UR; Bill Clinton  &LR; as the person who most symbolizes
what is wrong with our nation's moral values; second place was
occupied by  &UR; Jerry Springer &LR; , who got 27 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MATTERS OF TASTE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Ruth Reichl &LR; , Gourmet magazine editor in chief, writes in
American Heritage that the most overrated traditional dish in
America is meat loaf. ``In my opinion it's just a lazy man's
hamburger. ... Real meat-eaters want their stuff charred and juicy;
this is just so much gray dust.''
</P>
<P>
   As to the most underrated traditional dish, Reichl names the
peanut butter and jelly sandwich. ``It's the perfect American dish:
sweet, salty, soft, chewy. It's also infinitely portable.
Relegating this wonderful invention to the school lunch is a
terrible waste.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S.: Rover Bar is ``the first all-natural performance snack
concocted exclusively for dogs,'' says Men's Journal. The
manufacturer of this health snack also makes a wheat-free variety
for dogs with food allergies.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INDIGENTS NEED NOT APPLY &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The State Bar of California has new San Francisco headquarters,
in a 13-story building near the Embarcadero Center, but it occupies
only half the space in the building. California Lawyer reports that
the bar is seeking to rent the unused area, ``but it only wants to
rent to top-dollar customers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hence, the decision by bar governors in March to stay away
from charitable legal service organizations, which often have
cash-flow problems and might want discounts.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``There are certainly other men I can think of as better
candidates for sexiest man: Mikhail Gorbachev. I can't answer for
women, but I find him very attractive as a man's man. He has an
extraordinary combination of intelligence, baldness and serenity.
Almost Buddha-like.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Sean Connery, former sexiest man, in the British magazine
Midweek.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
