<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Thursday, May
6, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-ROCKET (Seattle) _ When Boeing's new Delta 3 rocket
misfired on Tuesday night, it was not only a major setback for
Boeing and its important Delta 3 program, but it was a setback for
U.S. attempts to win back a majority of the space launch business
from the Europeans. Officials say the Delta 3 $230 million mission
is a total failure. The communications satellite cannot be saved.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-GUMBEL (Undated) _ So Bryant ``Will You Still Respect Me in
the Morning?'' Gumbel is going back to the breakfast shift. Why,
you ask, would he return to the ham-and-eggs scene after tasting
USDA prime-time?
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-CASCADE (Undated) _ In James Martin's book, ``North
Cascades Crest: Notes and Images from America's Alps,'' Washington
state's Cascade mountains have found an author with music in his
soul and a photographer steeped in swirling clouds and distinctive
North Cascades light.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Cleveland) _ Seattle Mariners play the Cleveland
Indians.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-VECSEY-COLUMN _ Column on the Seattle SuperSonics.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
