<SLUG> BC-OUT-BOATING-SIDE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT BOAT SELLERS DON'T TELL YOU
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEREMY BAGOTT  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Jack Tyler wishes he had understood the concept of
dealer ``flooring'' (begin ital)before(end ital) he bought two new
boats years ago.
</P>
<P>
   A flooring cost is a fee the dealer pays the manufacturer for
taking delivery of a boat to be displayed on the lot. This gives
the dealer a chance to show many models without having to actually
buy them. A flooring cost of about $40 per month per $10,000 of
boat is typically paid _ and figured into the dealer's overhead.
</P>
<P>
   ``If the boat dealer is allowed X amount of capital or feels he
can afford no more, then that defines the inventory he can put on
his floor,'' said Tyler, a St. Petersburg, Fla., boater who has
researched the topic extensively. ``The more expensive the models
he selects, the fewer he can show. Or the more low-end the models
he selects, the harder to demo the big boys.''
</P>
<P>
   The typical buyer will look at a showroom model for
demonstration purposes, but, when buying, will put a deposit on a
yet-to-be-built boat. This costs the dealer next to nothing. When
the buyer's boat arrives, it is commissioned for some time in the
yard, where it can be viewed by other potential buyers without
tying up any flooring capital for the dealer.
</P>
<P>
   The boater may be better served by waiting until boating season
ends, when the dealer might be more willing to bargain if his
showroom models haven't sold. At that point, he may have to prolong
the financing arrangement with the builder, or even buy the
demonstration boat outright _ something the dealer (begin
ital)really(end ital) doesn't want to do. This is when a good deal
can be made.
</P>
<P>
   To determine when a showroom model was built _ and how long the
dealer has probably been sitting on it _ look at the hull
identification number on the transom; the month and year of
manufacture are found in the last four numbers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
