r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT     05-05 0080
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-KOSOVO-MASSACRE-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ```We will protect you,' they promised, and then when the army
came, our own Serbs put on masks and joined in the butchery. They
knew who to single out. They knew who had money.''
</P>
<P>
   _MAGRIBE NEZIRI, an Albanian Kosovar from Slovinje, telling of
the villagers' role in a massacre there.
</P>
</TEXT>
