Volunteers sort clothing Wednesday at the Oakcrest Church of Christ
in Oklahoma City. The items had been donated for victims of
Monday's tornadoes, which destroyed housands of homes here and
killed at least 43 people in Oklahoma and Kansas. More twisters
swarmed across parts of Texas and Arkansas on Tuesday, killing one
more person. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) OKLAHOMA City -- May 5, 1999 -- OKLA-STORM-1, 5-05 --
Sofas are used as beds by people who evacuated their homes or were
left homeless by tornadoes at the Oakcrest Church of Christ on
Wednesday. People who fled neighborhoods that suffered the worst
damage in Oklahoma's deadliest tornadoes in five decades started
returning on Wednesday, many of them finding only rubble where
their homes had stood. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- May 5, 1999 -- CIR-MUSEUM-GUIDES, 5-05 --
Maxwell Anderson, director of the Whitney Museum, demonstrates a
