Victory Theater. In acts that often trace their origins to the
harvest festivals of more than 2,000 years ago, this youthful,
handsome and graceful company spends a swift two hours in a range
of demanding performances, most of them typifying Chinese circus
and constituting a refreshing alternative to the Western tradition.
(Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
