assembly plant, the headquarters of PalTel, the Mideast's first
privately owned phone company. The investments can be considered
cornerstones of an emerging Palestinian economy, which is being
built with offshore Palestinian money in anticipation of statehood.
(Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo)
