<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:MOVIES:TWIN-DRAGONS-art-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MOVIE REVIEW: ``TWIN DRAGONS'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of a scene from the movie ``Twin
Dragons,'' starring Jackie Chan. (Credit: Copyright 1999 Dimension
Films.) 
 By EVAN SUSTAIRE 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``TWIN DRAGONS''
</P>
<P>
   Starring: Jackie Chan, Maggie Cheung and Teddy Robin.
</P>
<P>
   Plot: Twin brothers are separated at birth in a semi-freak
accident. One grows up in America living the sweet life while the
other toughs it out in the streets of Hong Kong. When they are
adults they run into each other and become entwined in each other
lives.
</P>
<P>
   Why go see it: ``Twin Dragons'' is a movie only for die-hard
Jackie Chan fans. Its dubbed voices are not much better than the
old Godzilla movies. If you enjoy decent karate action this film
might be for you.
</P>
<P>
   Reasons for rating: The PG-13 is for violence and mild sex
scenes.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 6.5.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
