<SLUG> BC-KIDS:HOROSCOPE-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): Your worries do not seem to be worth
the hassle lately, but your perseverance will set an example for
those who look up to you. You can make it through this rough time
in your life if you maintain a positive attitude. The choice is
yours and nobody else's. Choose wisely.
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): Quit putting things off. If you have
the spare time, force yourself to get the chores over with so you
can get to the more entertaining activities. Turn your radio on and
``whistle while you work.'' You can make the work fun and get it
over with, then go play.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): A drastic change is approaching.
Open your eyes, and you will be able to picture it. Take this as a
warning because it may take some getting used to. If you can
picture it, the mental preparations will make it easier to accept.
</P>
<P>
   LEO (July 23 - Aug. 22): People do not appreciate the
supercilious attitude you have been giving off lately. Believe it
or not, you do not know everything about everything. Humble
yourself before your attitude puts you in a humbling situation.
This may be hard, but those who matter most to you will notice and
like it.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGO (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): You will be soaring to great heights
in the next few weeks. Your positive attitude and optimism is
taking you places you have never been before. The smile you are
wearing will help you achieve a goal.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRA (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): You will never get anything more out
of something than what you put into it. Give everything that you do
a wholehearted attempt rather than loafing off and just muddling
through. Your whole life will be much more exciting and you will
learn more than you ever thought imaginable.
</P>
<P>
   SCORPIO (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): This week will not appear to be one
of your better ones at first, but it will be one that you will want
to repeat. This week will be extremely clear and productive, but
your friends' attitudes could overwhelm you and your good mood. Try
to help them, but do not let them bog you down.
</P>
<P>
   SAGITTARIUS (Nov. 22 - Dec. 21): There is some spectacular news
waiting for you at the end of the week. Share your news with
everybody. Something that you have always wanted to come true might
actually be starting to come around. Do not get so caught up with
this that you shun your friends and what they have to say.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): One day this week, you will be
struck by a brilliant idea that could change the way you feel about
something. Before you forget it, write it down, tell a friend or
both. Most awesome ideas are lost in the business of every day, but
that is not going to happen to you. While it is still fresh in your
head, take time to completely think it out.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): Take your cutie somewhere out of
the ordinary this weekend. Get all dressed up and make a date out
of it. Even if there is nothing to celebrate, celebrate just for
the fun of it. Watch for some side-effects of slight depression in
your friend. If it's caught early, depression is much easier to
handle.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): You will surprise yourself this
week. You might find yourself being the analyst in your class
discussions, or you might hit that high note in full voice. Pat
yourself on the back and then try to go further with what you have
done. Do not settle.
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April 19): You will discover the inspiration
that you have been searching for the past month or so. The school
year is nearing its end, but it ain't over till the fat lady sings
(or something along those lines). Your lack of motivation will be
temporarily revived, so you can make it through the rest of the
year.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
