<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:NEWS-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A BRIEF LOOK AT THE NEWS 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 c. 1999 Compiled from reports by The Associated Press and Fort
Worth Star-Telegram. 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HIGHWAY SMASH-UP
</P>
<P>
   COLTON, Calif. _ A sudden storm, high speeds and rush-hour
traffic led to multiple pileups that left about 70 people injured
and 150 vehicles mangled along a stretch of Interstate 10 on April
28, authorities said. Wreckage was scattered for miles, but no
deaths were reported. At least 67 people were taken to hospitals;
others were treated at the scene. Some collisions involved more
than 25 vehicles. Heavy rain, hail and winds up to 50 mph were
reported in the area.
</P>
<P>
   IS DEION DONE?
</P>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Dallas Cowboy Deion Sanders underwent surgery
Wednesday on his injured left big toe and is expected to begin an
aggressive, four- to six-month period of rehabilitation in three
weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Jones, the Cowboys' owner, wouldn't speculate on when
Sanders will return. He did say the All-Pro cornerback might miss
all of training camp and perhaps the start of the season. Jones
also said the injury means Sanders can't play wide receiver. ``We
are going to prepare our team like Deion is not going to be
there,'' Jones said.
</P>
<P>
   BAGGAGE THIEVES ARRESTED
</P>
<P>
   GRAPEVINE, Texas _ Ten baggage handlers have been arrested in
connection with the thefts of thousands of dollars' worth of items
from luggage passing through Dallas/Fort Worth International
Airport. The handlers, who work in the baggage sorting and cargo
holding areas, are suspected of stealing items from about 500 bags.
The case is under investigation.
</P>
<P>
   MANSON CUTS TOUR SHORT
</P>
<P>
   CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa _ Shock rocker Marilyn Manson cut short his
concert and abruptly walked off the stage when he realized someone
had stuck a large yellow smiley face on a stage prop. The resulting
rowdiness ended in 23 arrests.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd of 4,765 appeared stunned when Manson _ already the
target of criticism this week alleging that his wild, ``gothic''
style influenced the Littleton, Colo., school shooting _ became
angry Wednesday and stormed off the stage early. Some in the crowd
became rowdy and swarmed Manson's tour bus.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, hundreds of demonstrators rallied outside a Manson
concert in Minneapolis, protesting possible links between his dark
music and the Colorado school killings. At the same time, Manson
announced the cancellation of next week's last five dates of his
U.S. tour, saying it was out of respect for the victims of the
shootings.
</P>
<P>
   Manson, who took his stage name from Marilyn Monroe and mass
killer Charles Manson, said he blames the tragedy on ignorance,
hatred and access to guns.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
